INSERT INTO `agent_messages` VALUES (1,'GENERAL','How can I improve my resume?','2026-02-26 16:09:05.522333',NULL,'USER',1),(2,'GENERAL','Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. Here are some suggestions for improvement:\n\n*   **Summary:** Tailor your summary to specific job descriptions. Instead of a generic statement, highlight the skills and experiences that align with the requirements of the jobs you\'re applying for. Consider quantifying your achievements here as well.\n*   **Education:** Consider including your GPA if it\'s above 3.5. If you have relevant coursework, you can list 2-3 of the most relevant courses to the jobs you are applying for.\n*   **Experience:** While your Starbucks experience demonstrates management skills, try to emphasize data-related aspects. For example, quantify how you improved efficiency or customer satisfaction using data analysis. Use action verbs to start each bullet point.\n*   **Projects:** This is a strong section! Make sure each project bullet point clearly demonstrates the problem, your approach, and the results. Consider adding a link to a portfolio or GitHub if applicable.\n*   **Technical Skills:** Categorize your skills more granularly (e.g., Programming Languages, Data Analysis Tools, Cloud Technologies). This makes it easier for ATS to parse and recruiters to quickly identify your expertise. Consider adding skills like Python or R if you have them.\n*   **Achievements:** Great to have this section! Quantify your achievements whenever possible. Think about adding other achievements, especially those related to data analysis or problem-solving.\n*   **Formatting:** Consider using a more modern resume template. While LaTeX is great, many ATS systems parse simpler formats (like .docx) more reliably. Ensure consistent formatting throughout.\n\nOverall, focus on quantifying your accomplishments and tailoring your resume to each specific job description. Let me know if you\'d like me to elaborate on any of these points!','2026-02-26 16:09:10.170721','{\"message\": \"Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. Here are some suggestions for improvement:\\n\\n*   **Summary:** Tailor your summary to specific job descriptions. Instead of a generic statement, highlight the skills and experiences that align with the requirements of the jobs you\'re applying for. Consider quantifying your achievements here as well.\\n*   **Education:** Consider including your GPA if it\'s above 3.5. If you have relevant coursework, you can list 2-3 of the most relevant courses to the jobs you are applying for.\\n*   **Experience:** While your Starbucks experience demonstrates management skills, try to emphasize data-related aspects. For example, quantify how you improved efficiency or customer satisfaction using data analysis. Use action verbs to start each bullet point.\\n*   **Projects:** This is a strong section! Make sure each project bullet point clearly demonstrates the problem, your approach, and the results. Consider adding a link to a portfolio or GitHub if applicable.\\n*   **Technical Skills:** Categorize your skills more granularly (e.g., Programming Languages, Data Analysis Tools, Cloud Technologies). This makes it easier for ATS to parse and recruiters to quickly identify your expertise. Consider adding skills like Python or R if you have them.\\n*   **Achievements:** Great to have this section! Quantify your achievements whenever possible. Think about adding other achievements, especially those related to data analysis or problem-solving.\\n*   **Formatting:** Consider using a more modern resume template. While LaTeX is great, many ATS systems parse simpler formats (like .docx) more reliably. Ensure consistent formatting throughout.\\n\\nOverall, focus on quantifying your accomplishments and tailoring your resume to each specific job description. Let me know if you\'d like me to elaborate on any of these points!\", \"suggestions\": [\"Let\'s refine the bullet points in your Starbucks experience to highlight data analysis skills.\", \"I can help you tailor your summary to a specific job description.\", \"Show me some modern resume templates suitable for data analyst roles.\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"IMPROVE_BULLET\"}','ASSISTANT',1),(3,'GENERAL','which first i change','2026-02-26 16:09:43.261433',NULL,'USER',1),(4,'GENERAL','Given your current resume and the previous feedback, I recommend starting with the **Technical Skills** section. Categorizing your skills more granularly will make it easier for ATS systems and recruiters to identify your expertise. After that, focus on tailoring your **Summary** to specific job descriptions. This will make a significant impact on how well your resume is received.','2026-02-26 16:09:46.489643','{\"message\": \"Given your current resume and the previous feedback, I recommend starting with the **Technical Skills** section. Categorizing your skills more granularly will make it easier for ATS systems and recruiters to identify your expertise. After that, focus on tailoring your **Summary** to specific job descriptions. This will make a significant impact on how well your resume is received.\", \"suggestions\": [\"Let\'s start with the Technical Skills section. Can you list out your skills and I\'ll help you categorize them?\", \"Show me a job description you\'re targeting, and I\'ll help you tailor your summary.\", \"Can you give me some more details about your experience with Python or R?\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"ADVICE\"}','ASSISTANT',1),(5,'GENERAL','can you provide example for real skill i can add','2026-02-26 16:10:15.462456',NULL,'USER',1),(6,'GENERAL','Okay, based on your current resume and the role of a Junior Data Analyst, here are some specific skills you could add to your Technical Skills section to make it more appealing to both ATS and human recruiters. I\'ve categorized them for clarity:\n\n*   **Programming Languages:** Python, R (These are highly valuable for data analysis. Even basic proficiency is worth mentioning.)\n*   **Data Analysis Tools:** Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn (Python libraries), RStudio (If you know R), Tableau, Power BI (More advanced data visualization tools)\n*   **Databases:** PostgreSQL, MySQL (More robust database management systems than just SQL in general)\n*   **Cloud Technologies:** AWS (Amazon Web Services), Azure, Google Cloud Platform (Familiarity with cloud platforms is a plus, especially if you\'ve used them for data storage or analysis)\n*   **Statistical Software:** SPSS, SAS (If you have experience with these, definitely include them)\n\nEven if you only have a basic understanding of some of these, listing them shows initiative and a willingness to learn. Make sure to tailor the skills you list to the specific requirements of the jobs you\'re applying for. For example, if a job description mentions Python and Pandas, make sure those are prominently featured on your resume.','2026-02-26 16:10:19.006465','{\"message\": \"Okay, based on your current resume and the role of a Junior Data Analyst, here are some specific skills you could add to your Technical Skills section to make it more appealing to both ATS and human recruiters. I\'ve categorized them for clarity:\\n\\n*   **Programming Languages:** Python, R (These are highly valuable for data analysis. Even basic proficiency is worth mentioning.)\\n*   **Data Analysis Tools:** Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn (Python libraries), RStudio (If you know R), Tableau, Power BI (More advanced data visualization tools)\\n*   **Databases:** PostgreSQL, MySQL (More robust database management systems than just SQL in general)\\n*   **Cloud Technologies:** AWS (Amazon Web Services), Azure, Google Cloud Platform (Familiarity with cloud platforms is a plus, especially if you\'ve used them for data storage or analysis)\\n*   **Statistical Software:** SPSS, SAS (If you have experience with these, definitely include them)\\n\\nEven if you only have a basic understanding of some of these, listing them shows initiative and a willingness to learn. Make sure to tailor the skills you list to the specific requirements of the jobs you\'re applying for. For example, if a job description mentions Python and Pandas, make sure those are prominently featured on your resume.\", \"suggestions\": [\"Let\'s refine your summary to highlight these new skills.\", \"Should we update your project descriptions to showcase these skills in action?\", \"Can you provide a job description you\'re targeting so I can tailor the skills list further?\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"IMPROVE_BULLET\"}','ASSISTANT',1),(7,'GENERAL','How can I improve my resume?','2026-02-27 16:12:07.133892',NULL,'USER',2),(8,'GENERAL','Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. Here are some areas we can improve:\n\n*   **Summary:** It\'s a bit generic. Let\'s make it more impactful by quantifying your achievements and tailoring it to specific roles you\'re applying for.\n*   **Experience:** The bullet points under \'TechCorp\' are weak. We need to use the STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result) to showcase your accomplishments and the value you brought to the company. \"new Application\" is not descriptive.\n*   **Projects:** These are good, but we can add more detail about the challenges you faced and how you overcame them. Also, quantify the impact of your project if possible (e.g., number of users, performance improvements).\n*   **Technical Skills:** This section is well-organized. Consider adding specific libraries or tools you\'re proficient with under each category to make it more ATS-friendly.\n*   **Formatting:** The LaTeX template is clean, but ensure it\'s easily parsable by ATS systems. Consider exporting to PDF/TXT format for submission.\n\nTo help me give you the best advice, could you tell me about a specific job you\'re targeting? Or, are there any specific sections you\'d like to focus on improving first?','2026-02-27 16:12:11.990364','{\"message\": \"Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. Here are some areas we can improve:\\n\\n*   **Summary:** It\'s a bit generic. Let\'s make it more impactful by quantifying your achievements and tailoring it to specific roles you\'re applying for.\\n*   **Experience:** The bullet points under \'TechCorp\' are weak. We need to use the STAR method (Situation, Task, Action, Result) to showcase your accomplishments and the value you brought to the company. \\\"new Application\\\" is not descriptive.\\n*   **Projects:** These are good, but we can add more detail about the challenges you faced and how you overcame them. Also, quantify the impact of your project if possible (e.g., number of users, performance improvements).\\n*   **Technical Skills:** This section is well-organized. Consider adding specific libraries or tools you\'re proficient with under each category to make it more ATS-friendly.\\n*   **Formatting:** The LaTeX template is clean, but ensure it\'s easily parsable by ATS systems. Consider exporting to PDF/TXT format for submission.\\n\\nTo help me give you the best advice, could you tell me about a specific job you\'re targeting? Or, are there any specific sections you\'d like to focus on improving first?\", \"suggestions\": [\"Let\'s rewrite the bullet points for your \'TechCorp\' experience using the STAR method.\", \"Help me tailor my summary to a specific job description.\", \"Suggest improvements to my \'Projects\' section.\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"IMPROVE_BULLET\"}','ASSISTANT',2),(9,'GENERAL','Help me tailor my summary to a specific job description.','2026-02-27 16:14:48.311320',NULL,'USER',2),(10,'GENERAL','Okay, I can help you tailor your summary to a specific job description. Please provide the job description so I can identify the key skills and experiences the employer is looking for. Once you provide the job description, I will rewrite your summary to highlight the most relevant qualifications and make it more appealing to the hiring manager. I will focus on quantifying your achievements and using keywords from the job description.','2026-02-27 16:14:51.383325','{\"message\": \"Okay, I can help you tailor your summary to a specific job description. Please provide the job description so I can identify the key skills and experiences the employer is looking for. Once you provide the job description, I will rewrite your summary to highlight the most relevant qualifications and make it more appealing to the hiring manager. I will focus on quantifying your achievements and using keywords from the job description.\", \"suggestions\": [\"Provide the job description.\", \"Let\'s work on improving your experience section next.\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"MATCH_JOB\"}','ASSISTANT',2),(11,'GENERAL','How can I improve my resume?','2026-02-27 16:55:24.335859',NULL,'USER',3),(12,'GENERAL','Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. Here are some suggestions for improvement:\n\n*   **Quantify your achievements:** Instead of just saying you \'Developed a basic calculator application,\' try to quantify the impact or scope. For example, \'Developed a user-friendly calculator application in Java, resulting in a 20% increase in user engagement during testing.\'\n*   **Tailor your summary:** Customize your summary for each job you apply for. Highlight the skills and experiences that are most relevant to the specific role.\n*   **Expand on your skills:** Instead of just listing skills, provide context or examples of how you\'ve used them. For example, under Git, you could add \'Used Git for version control and collaboration on team projects.\'\n*   **Add more projects or experiences:** If you have any other projects, volunteer work, or relevant coursework, include them to showcase your skills and interests.\n*   **Consider adding a skills-based section:** If you have significant skills that aren\'t reflected in your project descriptions, consider adding a dedicated \'Skills\' section where you can elaborate on your proficiency.\n*   **Use action verbs:** Start your bullet points with strong action verbs to make them more impactful. For example, instead of \'Implemented arithmetic operations,\' try \'Engineered arithmetic operations.\'\n*   **Proofread carefully:** Ensure there are no typos or grammatical errors.\n\nI can help you with any of these areas in more detail. Would you like me to help you rewrite your bullet points to be more impactful?','2026-02-27 16:55:29.445809','{\"message\": \"Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. Here are some suggestions for improvement:\\n\\n*   **Quantify your achievements:** Instead of just saying you \'Developed a basic calculator application,\' try to quantify the impact or scope. For example, \'Developed a user-friendly calculator application in Java, resulting in a 20% increase in user engagement during testing.\'\\n*   **Tailor your summary:** Customize your summary for each job you apply for. Highlight the skills and experiences that are most relevant to the specific role.\\n*   **Expand on your skills:** Instead of just listing skills, provide context or examples of how you\'ve used them. For example, under Git, you could add \'Used Git for version control and collaboration on team projects.\'\\n*   **Add more projects or experiences:** If you have any other projects, volunteer work, or relevant coursework, include them to showcase your skills and interests.\\n*   **Consider adding a skills-based section:** If you have significant skills that aren\'t reflected in your project descriptions, consider adding a dedicated \'Skills\' section where you can elaborate on your proficiency.\\n*   **Use action verbs:** Start your bullet points with strong action verbs to make them more impactful. For example, instead of \'Implemented arithmetic operations,\' try \'Engineered arithmetic operations.\'\\n*   **Proofread carefully:** Ensure there are no typos or grammatical errors.\\n\\nI can help you with any of these areas in more detail. Would you like me to help you rewrite your bullet points to be more impactful?\", \"suggestions\": [\"Rewrite bullet points to be more impactful.\", \"Tailor the summary to a specific job description.\", \"Expand on skills with context and examples.\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"ADVICE\"}','ASSISTANT',3),(13,'GENERAL','suggest me the improvemnet','2026-03-07 18:03:08.549362',NULL,'USER',4),(14,'GENERAL','Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. It\'s a great start! Here are some areas we can focus on to make it even stronger:\n\n*   **Quantify, Quantify, Quantify:** You\'ve started doing this, which is excellent! Let\'s see if we can add numbers and metrics to *every* bullet point. For example, instead of \'Engineered a predictive demand forecasting system using Google Gemini AI...\', try \'Engineered a predictive demand forecasting system using Google Gemini AI, achieving a 15% improvement in forecast accuracy compared to the previous model.\'\n*   **Tailor to Specific Jobs:** While your resume showcases impressive skills, it\'s currently quite general. To maximize your chances, tailor it to each specific job you apply for. Analyze the job description and highlight the skills and experiences that are most relevant.\n*   **Summary Enhancement:** Your summary is good, but it could be more impactful. Instead of just listing skills, try to weave them into a compelling narrative that showcases your value proposition. Think about what makes you unique and what you can offer a potential employer.\n*   **Consider a Skills Section Restructure:** The skills section is a bit dense. Consider breaking it down further into categories like \'Backend\', \'Frontend\', \'AI/ML\', \'DevOps\' to improve readability and ATS compatibility.\n*   **Project Details:** For each project, consider adding a \'Key Achievement\' or \'Impact\' bullet point that summarizes the overall benefit of your work. This helps the reader quickly understand the value you brought to the project.\n\nWhich of these areas would you like to focus on first? Or, if you have a specific job description in mind, I can help you tailor your resume to it.','2026-03-07 18:03:14.004948','{\"message\": \"Okay, I\'ve reviewed your resume. It\'s a great start! Here are some areas we can focus on to make it even stronger:\\n\\n*   **Quantify, Quantify, Quantify:** You\'ve started doing this, which is excellent! Let\'s see if we can add numbers and metrics to *every* bullet point. For example, instead of \'Engineered a predictive demand forecasting system using Google Gemini AI...\', try \'Engineered a predictive demand forecasting system using Google Gemini AI, achieving a 15% improvement in forecast accuracy compared to the previous model.\'\\n*   **Tailor to Specific Jobs:** While your resume showcases impressive skills, it\'s currently quite general. To maximize your chances, tailor it to each specific job you apply for. Analyze the job description and highlight the skills and experiences that are most relevant.\\n*   **Summary Enhancement:** Your summary is good, but it could be more impactful. Instead of just listing skills, try to weave them into a compelling narrative that showcases your value proposition. Think about what makes you unique and what you can offer a potential employer.\\n*   **Consider a Skills Section Restructure:** The skills section is a bit dense. Consider breaking it down further into categories like \'Backend\', \'Frontend\', \'AI/ML\', \'DevOps\' to improve readability and ATS compatibility.\\n*   **Project Details:** For each project, consider adding a \'Key Achievement\' or \'Impact\' bullet point that summarizes the overall benefit of your work. This helps the reader quickly understand the value you brought to the project.\\n\\nWhich of these areas would you like to focus on first? Or, if you have a specific job description in mind, I can help you tailor your resume to it.\", \"suggestions\": [\"Let\'s refine the bullet points in my \'Ats Resify\' project.\", \"Help me tailor my resume to a specific job description.\", \"Suggest improvements to my summary section.\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"IMPROVE_BULLET\"}','ASSISTANT',4),(15,'GENERAL','mostly i apply for SDE or SDE intern so suggest me the summary according to this role','2026-03-07 18:05:29.811556',NULL,'USER',4),(16,'GENERAL','Okay, I can help you refine your summary to better target SDE and SDE intern roles. Here are a few options, focusing on different aspects you might want to emphasize:\n\n**Option 1 (Focus on Full-Stack & AI):**\n\"Enthusiastic Computer Science student with a strong foundation in Java, data structures and algorithms, and object-oriented design. Experienced in developing scalable full-stack applications, with a passion for integrating AI solutions to improve system performance and user experience. Proven ability to collaborate effectively in team environments to deliver high-quality, reliable software.\"\n\n**Option 2 (Focus on Problem Solving & Impact):**\n\"Highly motivated Computer Science student seeking an SDE role. Proficient in Java and experienced in building full-stack applications using Spring Boot and React. Adept at applying data structures and algorithms to solve complex problems, as demonstrated by solving 500+ coding challenges. Eager to contribute to a team and build innovative solutions.\"\n\n**Option 3 (Focus on Specific Technologies & Cloud):**\n\"Computer Science student with hands-on experience in Java, Spring Boot, React, and cloud technologies like AWS. Proven ability to design, develop, and deploy scalable applications, as demonstrated by projects involving AI-driven resume generation and medical supply chain optimization. Seeking an SDE role to leverage my skills in building robust and efficient software solutions.\"\n\nChoose the option that best reflects your strengths and the requirements of the specific roles you\'re targeting. We can also further customize any of these options!','2026-03-07 18:05:34.572081','{\"message\": \"Okay, I can help you refine your summary to better target SDE and SDE intern roles. Here are a few options, focusing on different aspects you might want to emphasize:\\n\\n**Option 1 (Focus on Full-Stack & AI):**\\n\\\"Enthusiastic Computer Science student with a strong foundation in Java, data structures and algorithms, and object-oriented design. Experienced in developing scalable full-stack applications, with a passion for integrating AI solutions to improve system performance and user experience. Proven ability to collaborate effectively in team environments to deliver high-quality, reliable software.\\\"\\n\\n**Option 2 (Focus on Problem Solving & Impact):**\\n\\\"Highly motivated Computer Science student seeking an SDE role. Proficient in Java and experienced in building full-stack applications using Spring Boot and React. Adept at applying data structures and algorithms to solve complex problems, as demonstrated by solving 500+ coding challenges. Eager to contribute to a team and build innovative solutions.\\\"\\n\\n**Option 3 (Focus on Specific Technologies & Cloud):**\\n\\\"Computer Science student with hands-on experience in Java, Spring Boot, React, and cloud technologies like AWS. Proven ability to design, develop, and deploy scalable applications, as demonstrated by projects involving AI-driven resume generation and medical supply chain optimization. Seeking an SDE role to leverage my skills in building robust and efficient software solutions.\\\"\\n\\nChoose the option that best reflects your strengths and the requirements of the specific roles you\'re targeting. We can also further customize any of these options!\", \"suggestions\": [\"Let\'s tailor the summary to a specific job description.\", \"Can you suggest improvements to my project descriptions?\", \"Help me restructure my skills section.\"], \"detectedIntent\": \"IMPROVE_BULLET\"}','ASSISTANT',4),(17,'GENERAL','write combination of three summary and write in short','2026-03-07 18:09:10.635079',NULL,'USER',4),(18,'GENERAL','Okay, here\'s a concise summary combining the best aspects of the previous options, tailor