L),(30,'2026-05-07 14:49:06.442234',0x00,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(31,'2026-05-09 00:27:56.960212',0x00,NULL,54,'Jude_Sipani_Resume.pdf.pdf','JUDE SIPANI  \nKOKOPO, 613, East New Britain Province, Papua New Guinea | judesipani310@gmail.com | 77269596 / 79004964 \n \nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY \nMotivated and detail-oriented graduate with a Bachelor of Sustainable Fisheries & Marine Resources from the Papua \nNew Guinea University of Natural Resources & Environment (PNG UNRE). Strong academic foundation in fisheries \nmanagement, marine conservation, post-harvest handling, HACCP food safety systems, and sustainability practices. \nDemonstrated interest in community-based conservation, environmental advocacy, and data-driven resource \nmanagement. Seeking an entry-level internship or graduate role to apply academic knowledge in a practical work \nenvironment.   \n \nSKILLS \nTechnical skills:  \n• Fisheries Management & Sustainability  \n• Marine Resource Conservation  \n• Post-Harvest Handling & Loss Management  \n• HACCP Principles & Food Safety Awareness  \n• Marine Ecosystem Monitoring  \n• Environmental Awareness & Advocacy  \n• Data Entry & Basic Data Analysis  \n• Research & Report Writing \n• Field Data Collection \n• Fisheries Software: FISAT II \nCore Competencies: Teamwork & Collaboration, Communication & Problem Solving \nTools & Platforms: MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint  \n \nACADEMIC & FIELD EXPERIENCE  \nStudent – Fisheries & Marine Science (Field & Knowledge Exposure)  \nPNG University of Natural Resources & Environment (UNRE)                                                       2022 – 2025  \n \n• Gained academic and practical exposure to fisheries management principles and sustainable resource use  \n• Studied post-harvest handling techniques and strategies to reduce post-harvest losses  \n• Learned HACCP systems, hazard identification, and food safety principles relevant to fisheries  \n• Participated in marine ecosystem awareness, monitoring, and conservation activities  \n• Conducted research assignments, data recording, and report preparation  \n• Developed teamwork, communication, and analytical skills through group projects and fieldwork  \n \nEXTRACURRICULAR & VOLUNTEER EXPERIENCE  \nMember  \nGreen Change Initiative – PNG UNRE                                                                                          2023 – 2025  \n• Promoted environmental awareness and sustainable behaviors  \n• Participated in conservation advocacy and student-led initiatives  \n• Supported awareness campaigns related to sustainability and climate responsibility  \nVolunteer  \nENB Sea Keepers                                                                                                                               2025  \n• Contributed to community-based marine conservation programs  \n• Assisted with environmental awareness activities and marine protection initiatives  \n• Supported teamwork in coastal and community engagement programs  \n \nEDUCATION  \nBachelor of Sustainable Fisheries & Marine Resources (Graduating with Distinction) \nPapua New Guinea University of Natural Resources & Environment                                                 2022 – 2025  \n \nADDITIONAL INFORMATION  \n• Strong interest in marine conservation, fisheries sustainability, and environmental management \n• Willing to undertake internships, field placements, and entry-level roles  \n• Able to work in team-based and community-focused environments  \n• Committed to continuous learning and professional development  \n \nREFEREES  \nMr. Vonklauss Siwat                                                                             Mr. Alex Nugi  \nLecturer – Marine Sciences, UNRE                                                        Farm Manager - UNRE Farm Operations \nTelephone 983 9144 | vaughnsiwat@gmail.com                                     Patron – Green Change Initiative  \n                                                                                                                 Mobile 7032 0096 | alexnugi14@gmail.com  \nMs. Emma Oliver  \nFounder & Director – ENB Sea Keepers  \nENB Marine Conservation Consultancy Services \nMobile 78378829 / 72420305 | oliveremma277@gmail.com | enbseakeepers@gmail.com \n \n','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"0/10\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided, so keyword matching is based on general industry relevance. The resume mentions \'Fisheries Management\', \'Marine Resource Conservation\', and \'Data Analysis\', but lacks more specific keywords related to data science or software engineering. Many relevant keywords are missing.\",\"suggestion\":\"Incorporate more specific keywords related to data analysis tools, programming languages, and relevant software if targeting data-related roles. Tailor the skills section to match the target job description.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"The formatting is generally clean with consistent font and spacing. However, the use of bullet points could be more consistent throughout the document. The contact information is clearly presented.\",\"suggestion\":\"Ensure consistent use of bullet points, especially in the \'Experience\' sections. Avoid excessive use of bolding or italics, which can sometimes confuse ATS systems.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume includes \'Skills\', \'Experience\', \'Education\', and \'Additional Information\'. It is missing a \'Summary\' section. The \'Extracurricular & Volunteer Experience\' section is present.\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a \'Summary\' section to highlight key skills and career goals. Consider adding a \'Projects\' or \'Certifications\' section to showcase practical experience and qualifications.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"1/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume primarily describes responsibilities rather than achievements. For example, \'Gained academic and practical exposure to fisheries management principles\' lacks quantifiable impact. \'Promoted environmental awareness and sustainable behaviors\' is vague and lacks metrics.\",\"suggestion\":\"Rewrite bullet points to focus on accomplishments and quantify impact whenever possible. Use strong action verbs and include metrics to demonstrate the value of your contributions.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"9/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is one page long and generally concise. Some bullet points could be tightened further to remove filler words.\",\"suggestion\":\"Review each bullet point and eliminate unnecessary words or phrases. Aim for maximum impact with minimal text.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided.\",\"suggestion\":\"No job description provided.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a professional summary highlighting key skills and career goals.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Rewrite bullet points to focus on achievements and quantify impact with metrics.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Incorporate specific keywords related to the target job description.\"},{\"section\":\"Impact\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Use strong action verbs to describe accomplishments.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Expand the skills section to include specific software and tools.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Proofread carefully for any typos or grammatical errors.\"}]'),(32,'2026-05-09 03:49:37.167088',0x00,1,64,'PraveenNew.pdf','Praveen Suthar\nVadodara, Gujarat | 8696928245 | praveensuthar1863@gmail.com | LinkedIn | GitHub | LeetCode\nSummary\nBackend-focused developer (Java, Spring Boot, React) with three production-deployed projects integrating AI APIs, Docker, and AWS.\nB.Tech CSE 2027, targeting SDE roles at product-based companies.\nEducation\nParul University Vadodara, Gujarat\nB.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering 2023 – 2027\nModern Defence Senior Secondary School Shivganj, Rajasthan\nHigher Secondary Certificate (HSC) 2022\nProjects\nATS Resify [Live]\nJava, Spring Boot, React, Gemini AI, AWS EC2, Docker, GitHub Actions\n- Built and deployed a full-stack AI resume generator using Java 22, Spring Boot 3, and Gemini AI; serves 54 active users across 6+\ncountries with 670+ events and 2m 03s avg session engagement.\n- Designed RESTful API with JWT and OAuth2 authentication; used Spring RestClient for dynamic prompt engineering with\nsub-2-second response times; ranks organically on Google, Bing, and DuckDuckGo with 12.8% bounce rate on core pages.\n- Automated build, test, and deployment pipeline using GitHub Actions and Docker to AWS EC2; eliminated manual deployment\nwith zero-downtime releases.\nMockMate [GitHub]\nJava 22, Spring Boot 3, LangChain4j, Gemini API, PostgreSQL, WebSocket, STOMP, Docker, React, TypeScript\n- Developed an AI-powered mock interview platform using Spring Boot 3, LangChain4j, and Gemini API; supports context-aware\nDSA problem generation and real-time feedback with sub-2-second latency.\n- Engineered a sandboxed code execution engine using Docker containers with isolated runtimes per submission; supports Java and\nPython with avg result delivery in 3–5 seconds; tracks solved problems per user via PostgreSQL to prevent question repetition.\n- Implemented real-time session synchronization using WebSocket and STOMP protocol; keeps chat transcripts, code output, and\nautomated phase transitions consistent across the full interview session.\nMediSync [GitHub]\nJava, Spring Boot, React, MySQL, PostgreSQL, Google OAuth 2.0\n- Integrated Gemini AI API for predictive demand forecasting across hospital zones; automated real-time inventory alerts reduced\nmanual monitoring overhead.\n- Built a redistribution algorithm that compares real-time stock levels against zone-specific demand thresholds; automatically flags\nsurplus inventory and triggers rerouting to high-demand zones without manual intervention.\n- Delivered a full-stack platform using Java Spring Boot and React with real-time inventory visibility; secured multi-admin access\nusing Google OAuth 2.0.\nTechnical Skills\nLanguages: Java 22, JavaScript (ES6+), TypeScript, Python, SQL, HTML/CSS\nFrameworks: Spring Boot, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, Spring MVC, Spring AI, React.js, LangChain4j\nDatabases: PostgreSQL, MySQL\nTools & DevOps: Docker, Git, GitHub Actions, AWS (EC2, S3), Maven, Postman, Linux\nConcepts: Data Structures & Algorithms, Object-Oriented Programming, RESTful API Design, System Design\nArchitecture & Testing: Microservices, CI/CD, WebSocket/STOMP, Unit Testing (JUnit 5)\nCertifications\n- AWS Academy Cloud Foundations – Amazon Web Services, 2025\n- IBM AI Fundamentals – IBM, 2025\nAchievements & Activities\n- Solved 500+ problems on LeetCode across arrays, trees, graphs, and dynamic programming; consistently optimize for both time and\nspace complexity.\n- Participated in Smart India Hackathon 2024; worked in a team of six to build and demo a functional prototype within a 24-hour\ndeadline.\n','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"5/10\",\"explanation\":\"Matched keywords include Java, Spring Boot, React, Docker, and AWS. Missing keywords are those related to specific SDE role requirements, such as testing frameworks beyond JUnit, specific cloud services, and monitoring tools. The resume focuses on project technologies rather than role-specific skills.\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor the skills section to match specific job descriptions, including relevant testing frameworks, cloud services, and monitoring tools.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"9/10\",\"explanation\":\"The formatting is generally clean and ATS-friendly, using standard section headers and bullet points. Minor inconsistencies might exist in spacing, but overall, it\'s well-structured.\",\"suggestion\":\"Ensure consistent spacing and font usage throughout the document for a polished look.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"Present sections: Contact, Education, Projects, Skills, Certifications, and Achievements. Missing: Summary/Objective.\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a concise summary or objective section to highlight career goals and key qualifications upfront.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"4/10\",\"explanation\":\"Bullet points describe responsibilities but lack hard metrics. For example, \\\"Built and deployed a full-stack AI resume generator...\\\" lacks quantifiable impact. \\\"Integrated Gemini AI API for predictive demand forecasting...\\\" also lacks specific results.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements by adding metrics such as percentage improvements, cost savings, or user growth numbers.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is concise and within a reasonable length. Some bullet points could be tightened further to remove unnecessary words.\",\"suggestion\":\"Review each bullet point and eliminate any filler words or redundant phrases to improve scannability.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided.\",\"suggestion\":\"No job description provided.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a summary highlighting key skills and career goals, targeting SDE roles.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements in project descriptions with specific metrics (e.g., user growth, performance improvements).\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Use stronger action verbs to describe responsibilities and contributions.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Include specific testing frameworks (e.g., Mockito, Selenium) and cloud monitoring tools (e.g., CloudWatch).\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Add soft skills like communication, teamwork, and problem-solving.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor keywords to match specific job descriptions, focusing on required skills and technologies.\"},{\"section\":\"Achievements\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Elaborate on the Smart India Hackathon project, highlighting the problem solved and the impact of the prototype.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Proofread for any typos or grammatical errors.\"}]'),(33,'2026-05-09 07:56:59.803002',0x01,24,57,'Addy_new_res.pdf','Addya Mishra\n940-720-5988 | adimishra021@gmail.com | LinkedIn | GitHub | LeetCode | Codeforces | CodeChef\nEducation\nParul University Vadodara, Gujarat\nBachelor in Computer Science (CGPA: 8.9/10) Aug 2023 – May 2027\nSt Aloysius Sr Sec. School Jabalpur, MP\nHigher Secondary Aug 2011 – May 2023\nProjects\nMovie Recommendation System | Python, Scikit-learn, Pandas, Streamlit | GitHub Feb 2025 – Mar 2025\n• Built an NLP-powered recommendation engine using bag-of-words and cosine similarity.\n• Processed movie dataset to generate personalized suggestions with cast & genre info.\n• Developed an interactive web app using Streamlit for seamless user experience.\nFake News Detection | Python, Scikit-learn, NLTK | GitHub Mar 2025 – Apr 2025\n• Built a machine learning model to classify news as real or fake with ∼90% accuracy.\n• Applied text preprocessing (tokenization, TF-IDF) and trained Logistic Regression & SVM models.\n• Evaluated performance using accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score metrics.\nRELTO – Smart Lost & Found Platform | Node.js, MongoDB, React, Mapbox | GitHub | LiveJan 2026 – Present\n• Built a real-time, map-based lost & found platform with geolocation pins and item discovery.\n• Implemented secure in-app chat tied to items with async conversations and unread tracking.\n• Designed a privacy-first contact flow by removing phone/email exposure.\n• Added item resolution workflow, abuse reporting, and audit trails.\nAchievements & Competitive Programming\n• Achieved Global Rank 70 in CodeChef Starters 165.\n• Attained Specialist on Codeforces with a highest rating of 1450.\n• Knight on LeetCode with a highest rating of 1952, ranking in the top 5% globally.\n• 3-Star Coder on CodeChef, among the top programmers in the university.\n• Solved over 2000 problems across Codeforces, LeetCode, and CodeChef.\n• Participated in 100+ rated contests across Codeforces, LeetCode, and CodeChef.\nTechnical Skills\nProgramming Languages: Java, Python, C/C++\nBackend Development: Node.js, Express, REST APIs, Socket.io, CI/CD Pipelines\nFrontend Technologies: HTML, CSS, JavaScript\nDatabases: MySQL, Oracle, MongoDB, PostgreSQL\nAI & Automation: Scikit-learn, NLTK, Pandas, NumPy, ServiceNow Platform Concepts\nTools & Platforms: Git, GitHub, VS Code, Streamlit, ServiceNow Instances, Unix Tools\nCertifications\nServiceNow Agentic AI Executive Micro-Certification Learning Path Oct 2025\nOracle Certified Professional: Java SE 17 Developer July 2025\nOracle Certified Professional: SQL/PLSQL Developer June 2025\nExtra-Curricular Activities\nCompetitive Programming Lead June 2025 – Present\nGDSC Parul University Vadodara, India\n• Mentored juniors and conducted workshops to improve problem-solving skills and contest performance.\n• Organized and managed coding contests, hackathons, and practice sessions for university students.\n• Developed and shared daily CP challenges, maintaining engagement across the community.\n','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"1/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume has very few keywords related to software development and high-frequency trading. Matched keywords include Python and Java. Missing keywords include: trading, finance, low latency, algorithms, market data, exchange connectivity, and risk management.\",\"suggestion\":\"Incorporate keywords related to software development and high-frequency trading into your resume, especially in the project descriptions and skills section. Focus on trading, finance, low latency, algorithms, market data, exchange connectivity, and risk management.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"9/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume uses clean bullets, consistent font/spacing, and standard section headers. It appears to be ATS-safe. Minor improvements could be made to spacing.\",\"suggestion\":\"Ensure consistent spacing throughout the document for improved readability.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume includes Education, Projects, Achievements, Skills, and Extra-Curricular Activities. It is missing a Summary section.\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a Summary section to highlight your key skills and experience relevant to the target role.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"2/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume lacks quantified achievements. For example, \'Built an NLP-powered recommendation engine using bag-of-words and cosine similarity\' doesn\'t provide any metrics. \'Mentored juniors and conducted workshops to improve problem-solving skills and contest performance\' is vague.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify your achievements with metrics (%, $, #, multipliers) to demonstrate impact. Use strong action verbs and focus on outcomes.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is one page and mostly concise. Some bullets could be tightened further.\",\"suggestion\":\"Review each bullet point and eliminate any filler words or redundant phrases.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"1/10\",\"explanation\":\"The candidate\'s experience is a significant mismatch for roles in software development and high-frequency trading. The projects are academic and lack direct relevance to the industry.\",\"suggestion\":\"Focus on projects and experiences that demonstrate skills relevant to software development and high-frequency trading. Highlight any experience with low-latency systems, market data, or trading algorithms.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a summary highlighting your interest and skills relevant to software development and high-frequency trading.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements in project descriptions using metrics to demonstrate impact.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Incorporate keywords related to trading, finance, low latency, and algorithms into your resume.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Use strong action verbs to describe your responsibilities and accomplishments.\"},{\"section\":\"Projects\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Focus on projects that demonstrate skills relevant to software development and high-frequency trading.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Include skills such as C++, Linux, distributed systems, and performance tuning.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor your resume to match the specific requirements of the target role.\"}]'),(34,'2026-05-09 12:19:46.608737',0x00,NULL,59,'Badreddine-Projets-LaTeX.pdf','Badreddine LADJEMI\nl Directeur de Projets & Programmes — Professional Services | MarTech · CRM · Salesforce · Data\n +33 6 24 33 44 42 | # badreddine@ankaboot.fr |  ankaboot.io | + Montreuil, France\nPROFIL\nDirecteur de projets et programmes IT avec plus de 15 ans d’expérience dans la direction opérationnelle de dispositifs de\ndelivery MarTech, CRM et Data, combinant pilotage du backlog, plan de charge, management d’équipes et coordination\ntransverse.\nEXPÉRIENCE\nIntermarché, Netto, Bricomarché (Groupe Les Mousquetaires) — CRM & Acquisition 2019 – 2026\nTeam Manager / Directeur Projets France\nDirection projets CRM, Marketing Automation et CDP pour Service Client, Fidélité, Média, e-Commerce des 5\nenseignes\nPilotage RFP et transformation Client échelle groupe ; management équipe tech/product de 6 personnes\nRationalisation stack MarTech, centre de services Salesforce, structuration backlog et plan de charge\nKPI : CAPEX >15 M€, ROI Acquisition x2, +20 utilisateurs hebdomadaires\nSodexo (Axys), GRDF (CGI) 2018 – 2019\nConsultant Digital Transformation France\nSodexo : Customer Journey B2B2C, Due Diligence SI, POS/OMS\nGRDF : Cahier des Charges CRM, Design Thinking\nBanque Africaine de Développement / Gvt Tunisie 2016 – 2018\nConsultant Projets e-Gov International\nMasterplan, architecture SI, RFP, PMO et design de services pour des programmes nationaux\nInteropérabilité SI, Justice Numérique, Mobile ID, CNAM\nSFR, TF1, VOO (via Beijaflore) 2011 – 2016\nConsultant Chef de Projet CRM France / Belgique\nSFR : AMOA Relation Client, Product Owner webmail et intégration Cloud\nVOO : Product Owner Selfcare ; UX/UI, spécifications, pilotage projets, recette, budget\nJWT / RMG Connect / Optimus 2009 – 2010\nChef de Projet e-Marketing France\nEmailing, Média/Ads, SEO, CRO, fundraising, e-commerce\nClients : WWF, Greenpeace, Croix-Rouge, Institut Curie, Motocab\nIngeniweb — Alterway 2005 – 2006\nDéveloppeur Fullstack Python France\nDéveloppement et intégration d’applications web Python/Zope\nCOMPÉTENCES CLÉS\nProfessional Services & Delivery : End-to-end delivery, backlog & capacity planning, plan de charge, centre de services\nrun/build, gouvernance, KPI delivery & adoption, Sales/Delivery, forecast à 3–6 mois\nTech & Data : Azure, GCP, AWS, Kubernetes, Python, TypeScript, SQL, Spark, Salesforce, Mediarithmics, Docker, Git\nIA : LiteLLM, OpenWebUI, NER, Prompt Engineering, Fine tuning, Alignment, Model benchmarking\nOutils : Jira, Office 365, GA4, Posthog, Figma, PowerPoint, Excel\nFORMATION & CERTIFICATIONS\nMines-Télécom Business School 2011\nMaster Grande École Paris, France\nCertifications : Leading SAFe · PRINCE2 Practitioner · Product Management · Boston University\nLANGUES & SECTEURS\nFrançais : Natif | Anglais : Fluent | Allemand : Grundlagen\nSecteurs : Retail · E-Commerce · Télécom · Médias · Énergie · eGov / Secteur Public / NGO\n','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"Matched: Salesforce, CRM, Data, Python. Missing: Project Management methodologies beyond PRINCE2 (e.g., Agile, Scrum), specific cloud platform skills (AWS Certified, Azure DevOps), and detailed MarTech stack experience beyond Salesforce and Mediarithmics.\",\"suggestion\":\"Incorporate Agile/Scrum methodologies, highlight specific cloud certifications, and expand on MarTech stack expertise.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"Generally clean, but the use of special characters (e.g., , ) and inconsistent spacing slightly detract from readability. The section headers are standard.\",\"suggestion\":\"Remove special characters and ensure consistent spacing throughout the document for better ATS parsing.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"Present: Contact, Experience, Skills, Education, Languages & Secteurs. Missing: Summary.\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a concise summary/profile section highlighting key skills and experience relevant to the target roles.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"4/10\",\"explanation\":\"Achievements are described but lack hard metrics. Example: \\\"Pilotage RFP et transformation Client échelle groupe ; management équipe tech/product de 6 personnes\\\". No quantifiable results are provided.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements with metrics. For example, rewrite \\\"Pilotage RFP et transformation Client échelle groupe\\\" to include cost savings or efficiency gains.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is two pages and could be more concise. Some bullet points are verbose. The experience section uses paragraphs instead of concise bullets.\",\"suggestion\":\"Reduce the resume to one page by trimming unnecessary details and converting paragraph descriptions into concise bullet points.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided.\",\"suggestion\":\"No job description provided.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a summary highlighting key skills and experience in project management, MarTech, and CRM.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements in each role with specific metrics (%, $, #) to demonstrate impact.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Convert paragraph descriptions in the experience section into concise bullet points.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Incorporate keywords related to Agile/Scrum methodologies and specific cloud platforms (AWS, Azure).\"},{\"section\":\"Brevity\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Reduce the resume to one page by trimming unnecessary details and focusing on key accomplishments.\"},{\"section\":\"Formatting\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Remove special characters and ensure consistent spacing for better ATS parsing.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor the resume to specific job descriptions by highlighting relevant skills and experience.\"}]'),(35,'2026-05-10 14:56:49.622871',0x01,NULL,57,'PraveenNew.pdf','Praveen Suthar\nVadodara, Gujarat | 8696928245 | praveensuthar1863@gmail.com | LinkedIn | GitHub | LeetCode\nSummary\nBackend-focused developer (Java, Spring Boot, React) with three production-deployed projects integrating AI APIs, Docker, and AWS.\nB.Tech CSE 2027, targeting SDE roles at product-based companies.\nEducation\nParul University Vadodara, Gujarat\nB.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering 2023 – 2027\nModern Defence Senior Secondary School Shivganj, Rajasthan\nHigher Secondary Certificate (HSC) 2022\nProjects\nATS Resify [Live]\nJava, Spring Boot, React, Gemini AI, AWS EC2, Docker, GitHub Actions\n- Built and deployed a full-stack AI resume generator using Java 22, Spring Boot 3, and Gemini AI; serves 54 active users across 6+\ncountries with 670+ ev