yed a full-stack AI resume generator using Java 22, Spring Boot 3, and Gemini AI; serves 54 active users across 6+\ncountries with 670+ events and 2m 03s avg session engagement.\n- Designed RESTful API with JWT and OAuth2 authentication; used Spring RestClient for dynamic prompt engineering with\nsub-2-second response times; ranks organically on Google, Bing, and DuckDuckGo with 12.8% bounce rate on core pages.\n- Automated build, test, and deployment pipeline using GitHub Actions and Docker to AWS EC2; eliminated manual deployment\nwith zero-downtime releases.\nMockMate [GitHub]\nJava 22, Spring Boot 3, LangChain4j, Gemini API, PostgreSQL, WebSocket, STOMP, Docker, React, TypeScript\n- Developed an AI-powered mock interview platform using Spring Boot 3, LangChain4j, and Gemini API; supports context-aware\nDSA problem generation and real-time feedback with sub-2-second latency.\n- Engineered a sandboxed code execution engine using Docker containers with isolated runtimes per submission; supports Java and\nPython with avg result delivery in 3–5 seconds; tracks solved problems per user via PostgreSQL to prevent question repetition.\n- Implemented real-time session synchronization using WebSocket and STOMP protocol; keeps chat transcripts, code output, and\nautomated phase transitions consistent across the full interview session.\nMediSync [GitHub]\nJava, Spring Boot, React, MySQL, PostgreSQL, Google OAuth 2.0\n- Integrated Gemini AI API for predictive demand forecasting across hospital zones; automated real-time inventory alerts reduced\nmanual monitoring overhead.\n- Built a redistribution algorithm that compares real-time stock levels against zone-specific demand thresholds; automatically flags\nsurplus inventory and triggers rerouting to high-demand zones without manual intervention.\n- Delivered a full-stack platform using Java Spring Boot and React with real-time inventory visibility; secured multi-admin access\nusing Google OAuth 2.0.\nTechnical Skills\nLanguage