ker, AWS (Cloud Foundations), Jupyter Notebook, VS Code, Vercel\nProjects\nMovie Recommender System 2025 – 2026\nPython, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Pickle\n– Built a content-based movie recommendation engine using TMDB 5000 movies dataset.\n– Used vectorization and cosine similarity to recommend movies based on genres, keywords, cast, and summaries.\n– Preprocessed and cleaned large-scale movie data using Pandas to improve recommendation accuracy.\n– Optimized similarity computation and reduced response time for faster recommendations.\n– Live Demo: link GitHub: link\nCredit Card Fraud Detection – Random Forest & SMOTE 2025 – 2026\nPython, Scikit-learn, imbalanced-learn, Pandas, NumPy, Pickle, Jupyter Notebook\n– Addressed extreme class imbalance using SMOTE on training data only, preventing data leakage.\n– Tuned Random Forest via RandomizedSearchCV (ROC-AUC metric); achieved 99.96% accuracy, 94.1% precision, 0.9545\nROC-AUC.\n– Exported production-ready .pkl model for integration into Flask/Django backends and real-time fraud detection APIs.\n– GitHub: link\nAI-Powered Crop Yield Prediction & Optimization 2025 – 2026\nPython, Django, Scikit-Learn, Together AI\n– Built an AI-based platform for crop yield prediction using Random Forest on district-level agricultural data.\n– Integrated LLM (Mistral/Mixtral) for smart farming recommendations and decision support.\n– Added weather insights, SMS alerts, and geo-location services for enhanced usability.\n– Performed data preprocessing and feature engineering to improve model accuracy and reliability.\n– Developed RESTful APIs using Django for seamless integration between frontend and ML models.\n– Live Demo: link GitHub: link\nAI-Powered SMS Spam Detection & Security Platform (SMSGUARD) 2025 – 2026\nPython, Flask, React.js, Scikit-learn, NLTK, TF-IDF, Framer Motion, Vercel\n– Built an end-to-end ML pipeline using Multinomial Naive Bayes, achieving 99.8% accuracy on 5,000+ SMS messages.\n– Designed a custom NLP preprocessing 