detection,\nconnecting the deep learning model to a React client via a Python/Flask server.\n– Tech Stack: React.js, Python, Flask, OpenCV, OCR.\n– GitHub: github.com/ArmanSingh-1/True-Copy\nCustomer Insights Dashboard 2025\n– Developed a full-stack web application using Flask and SQLAlchemy to provide dynamic customer segmentation\nanalysis. The platform allows users to upload CSV data and receive insights through distinct visualizations.\n– Implemented a RESTful API for handling user registration and login asynchronously.\n– Tech Stack: Flask, SQLAlchemy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, Jinja2, JavaScript.\n– GitHub: github.com/ArmanSingh-1/Hackathon-DashBoard\nTechnical Skills\nLanguages Python, C++, SQL, JavaScript, HTML/CSS\nWeb & Databases Flask, SQLAlchemy, REST APIs, SQLite, MongoDB, Jinja2, React.js\nData Science & AI Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn, OpenCV, OCR\nDeveloper Tools Git, VS Code, Jupyter Notebook, Linux, Power BI\nCS Fundamentals Data Structures, Algorithms, OOPs, DBMS, OS, Computer Networks\nCertifications & Achievements\n– Certificate in Ethical Hacking – AIITA (2023)\n– Computer Networks Certification – NPTEL (2025)\n– IELTS – Overall Band Score: 7.5 (2023)\nExtracurricular Activities\n– Member, Code Crafter: Actively participate in the official coding club of the IITM BS program.\n– Participant, Career Development Cell (CDC): Engage in Debates and active participation in writing\ncompetitions.\n\n\n--- Additional content recovered from PDF annotations and alternate parser ---\n+917861806976\nhttps://github.com/ArmanSingh-1\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/bhadoriya-arman-singh\nhttps://leetcode.com/u/Arman_Singh_74/\nhttps://www.codechef.com/users/arman_singh_47\nhttps://codeforces.com/profile/Arman_singh_\nhttps://github.com/ArmanSingh-1/True-Copy\nhttps://github.com/ArmanSingh-1/Hackathon-DashBoard','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"5/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume demonstrates some relevant skills, including Python, C++, Flask, and React.js. However, a job description would be needed to provide a more precise assessment of keyword alignment.\",\"suggestion\":\"Providing a job description would allow for a more accurate assessment of keyword alignment and identification of missing skills.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume has mostly clean formatting with consistent spacing. However, the summary is a dense paragraph instead of bullet points. The contact information is not properly formatted.\",\"suggestion\":\"Use bullet points in the summary and ensure consistent spacing throughout the resume. Use standard section headers.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"4/10\",\"explanation\":\"Present: Projects, Technical skills, Languages, Certifications. Missing: Contact, Summary/Objective, Education, Skills. The resume is missing several critical sections.\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a contact section with email and phone number. Add a summary/objective section. Add an education section with degree, university, and graduation date. Add a skills section.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"4/10\",\"explanation\":\"The project descriptions show \'what\' but not \'impact\'. Example: \'Engineered an AI Pipeline including computer vision pipeline to seamlessly extract and translate embedded text directly from images.\' This lacks specific metrics. Another example: \'Developed a full-stack web application using Flask and SQLAlchemy to provide dynamic customer segmentation analysis.\' This also lacks specific metrics.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify the impact of your projects by including metrics such as team size, user count, data volume, or performance improvements.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is 1 page long, but some sections could be more concise. The bullet points are generally concise.\",\"suggestion\":\"Review each section and remove any filler words or redundant information. Ensure all bullets are under two lines.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\",\"suggestion\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Education\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add an education section with your degree, university, and graduation date.\"},{\"section\":\"Impact\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify the impact of your projects by including metrics such as team size, user count, or performance improvements.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a skills section listing your technical skills, soft skills, and other relevant competencies.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Proofread the resume carefully to correct any spelling or grammar errors.\"}]'),(43,'2026-05-13 06:10:14.214009',0x00,NULL,59,'Scolasticah KarimI Gachungi is a CV.pdf','SCOLASTICAH KARIMI GACHUNGI \nMathematics/Business Studies Teacher \n \n karimiskawe1@gmail.com  +254721103664      Kenya                                                                                     \n                            \n \n \n \n \n \n \nProfessional Profile \nA zealous teacher of Mathematics/Business Studies subjects with 10+ years of experience in \ncontent delivery in secondary school education. With a track record of today’s methodologies \nto deliver quality and excellence towards students’ academic progress. Motivated to work with \ncolleagues by collaboration in order to develop new teaching strategies to help students. Adept \nin effective communication methods to positively live in harmonious environment by \nunderstanding each other, to meet the education objectives and laid down regulations and code \nof conduct for teachers. \n \nCareer Objectives \n To excel in my professional life at the highest level by utilizing my skills, knowledge and \nexperiences and contribute towards the accomplishment of given tasks.  \n To be employed in a challenging and learning environment for career progress. \n \nCore Skills \n English/Swahili Languages    Academic Evaluation  \n Secondary School Teacher     Results analysis and Reporting \n Lesson Planning      Student Centered-Learning \n Classroom Management     Curriculum Implementation  \n SEN Teaching Methods                            C  o  l l  a b  o  r  a t  i o  n   w   i t h   s t a  k  e    h  o  l d ers \n \nCareer/Work Experience  \nMay 2025 – Present     Musa Gitau Secondary School \n       Mathematics/Business Studies Teacher \nOutline  \n Responsible for teaching the Mathematics/Business Studies national curriculum for government \nschool. \n In charge of implementation of formulated policies for content delivery within the department. \n \nKey Responsibilities. \n Plan, organize and deliver engaging lessons that stimulate learners through quality instruction. \n Engage with colleagues to come up with modern pedagogical methods that enhance easy mastery \nof content. \n Collaborate with colleagues in evaluation, reporting and revising of tests and assignments. \n Plan educational field trip and other activities to enhance learning. \n Give remedial activities and materials for underperforming students toward their progress. \n Maintain professional personal records as well as students’ records including class attendance and \nacademic progress. \n Safeguard the welfare of students, staff members and other stake holders.    \n \nAchievements.   \n Designed teaching methods; audio listening, field trips and daily checking of assignment that \nmotivated students.  \n \n \nSeptember 2010 – May 2025   Mary Leakey Girls High School \nMathematics/Business Studies Teacher  Music Trainer \nOutline  \nTaught Mathematics/Business Studies in a public secondary school and presented the content using \na range of teaching techniques/methods to make it easier for students to understand.  \n  \nKey Responsibilities \n Prepared lesson plans, notes and other professional materials to ensure the syllabus is covered on \ntime. \n Impart knowledge, skills and positive attitudes to learners  \n Organized remedial actions to support learners with performance gaps. \n Taught mathematics/business studies and prepared students for National Examinations. \n Applied appropriate range of observation, assessment, evaluation and monitoring strategies for \nsetting learning objectives. \n Introduced new ideas and programs to ensure improvement in teaching and learning in the school. \n Embraced team work through collaborative methods to ensure consistency and improvement in \ncurriculum delivery. \n As Music Trainer, identified, natured and trained school team to participate in various \ncompetitions. \n \n  Achievements. \n Increase in performance of students in the national examinations to highest mean ever of 9.8 from \n8.4 \n Able to complete deadlines on time. \n Participated in Music Festivals competitions up to National level for several years. \n \nMarch 2017 – May 2025     Head of Boarding department \n Outline  \nIn charge of implementation of boarding policies and discipline in a public secondary school for \nconducive environment and stay of students. \nKey Responsibilities. \n Ensuring that student houses and their compounds are clean. \n Ensuring student discipline is maintained in the houses; sleeping and waking up on time. \n Liaise with parents/guardians on matters concerning boarding students\' conduct and welfare. \n Ensuring students maintain proper hygiene; personal cleanness and neatness in houses. \n Work with school leadership to improve the boarding experience and address challenges.   \n Develop and monitor structured routines for boarding students, including study schedules, meals, \nand extracurricular activities.  \n Overseeing the cleaning of dining hall, kitchen and its environs and meals are taken on time. \n Monitoring the quality of food on daily basis. \n Promote teamwork and leadership among the members of the department through mentorship. \n \n \n  \nJuly 2012 – May 2025     Head of Business Studies Subject \n Outline \nCoordinate other teachers in Business Studies in order to improve the performance of the subject. \nKey Responsibilities \n Come up with strategies to improve the performance of the subject. \n Popularize Business Studies subject to students to improve on numbers taking the subject. \n Conduct performance evaluations and professional development sessions for business studies \nstaff. \n Supervise and coordinate the business studies department to ensure the effective delivery of the \ncurriculum. \n Monitor the performance of teachers and students in business studies, analyzing results and \nimplementing improvement strategies. \n Organize subject meetings and workshops to foster collaboration and share teaching resources. \n Develop and procure teaching materials, textbooks, and resources for business studies. \n Ensure timely completion of syllabi and alignment with national education standards. \n Mentor and support teachers at subject level, offering guidance on pedagogy and assessment. \n Organize educational field trips. \nAchievements  \n Improvement of the subject performance within the school. \n Organized learning activities such as academic trips to popularize the subjects among students. \n Increase in number of students taking Business Studies subject. \n \nJanuary 2014 – May 2025     Member of Discipline Committee \n         Outline \n         Work with other committee members on over all discipline of the school. \n                Key Responsibilities \n Promote good behavior among the students and present those with good conduct for rewarding. \n Meet with misbehaving students and clarify the negative effects of bad behavior on their lives. \n Take suitable actions towards student’s misconduct. \n Liaise with parents/guardians on matters concerning students\' conduct and welfare. \n                Achievements  \n Able to maintain students discipline within the school. \n Informed parents/guardians on matters concerning student’s conduct and welfare.  \n \nEducation  \n \nEgerton University \nBachelor of Education (Arts) (Mathematics/Business Studies)  \n \nSecondary Education \nNguviu Girls High School \nKenya Certificate of Secondary Education School.  \n \nPrimary Education \nFirst Kenyan Evangel Academy \nKenya Certificate of Primary Education School.  \n \nTraining and Certification  \nSenior Management Course – Kenya School of Government (January – March 2026) \n \nCertificate in Project Management - European Business Institute (January 2023 - July 2024) \n \nCertificate in Curriculum Design and Instructional Decision Making - European Business \nInstitute (May 2023) \n \nCertificate in Human Resource Management - European Business Institute (March 2023) \n \nCertificate in The Youth, Peace and Security Primer - United Nations System Staff College \n(September 2023) \n \nCertificate in Foundation Primer on the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development (The SDG \nPrimer) - United Nations System Staff College (September 2023) \n \nCertificate in The Human Security Approach: From Principles to Practice - United Nations \nSystem Staff College (October 2023) \n \nCertificate in Women and Leadership - European Business Institute (October 2022) \n  \nCertificate in Leadership and Performance - Teachers Service commission. (Head of \nDepartments Work shop) (March 2018) \n \nCertificate in Leadership and Performance - Ministry of Education (February 2016) \n \n \n \n \n  \n \n \n     \n \n \n\n\n--- Additional content recovered from PDF annotations and alternate parser ---\n English/Swahili Languages\n Secondary School Teacher\n Lesson Planning\n Classroom Management\n SEN Teaching Methods\n Academic Evaluation\n Results analysis and Reporting\n Student Centered-Learning\n Curriculum Implementation\n Collaboration with stake holders','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"5/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume demonstrates some relevant skills for a teaching role, such as \'Lesson Planning\' and \'Curriculum Implementation\'. However, a job description would allow for a more precise keyword analysis.\",\"suggestion\":\"Providing a job description would allow for a more targeted keyword match and improve the score.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"5/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume has some formatting issues. The use of \'Outline\' and \'Key Responsibilities\' subheadings is unusual. The resume also uses inconsistent spacing and indentation. The resume is also 5 pages long, which is excessive.\",\"suggestion\":\"Use standard section headers and consistent formatting throughout. Reduce the resume to 2 pages maximum.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"6/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume includes Contact, Education, and Achievements sections. It is missing a Summary and Skills section.\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a professional summary at the beginning of the resume and a dedicated skills section.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"3/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume lacks quantified achievements. For example, \'Designed teaching methods; audio listening, field trips and daily checking of assignment that motivated students\' is descriptive but lacks metrics. \'Increase in performance of students in the national examinations to highest mean ever of 9.8 from 8.4\' is a good start, but more are needed.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements with metrics such as percentages, numbers, or specific results. Use strong action verbs to highlight accomplishments.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"1/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is 5 pages long and contains excessive detail. Many bullet points could be more concise.\",\"suggestion\":\"Trim the resume to 2 pages by removing redundant information and using concise language.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\",\"suggestion\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a professional summary highlighting key skills and experience in teaching.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify achievements in each role with specific metrics and results.\"},{\"section\":\"Formatting\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Improve formatting by using consistent spacing, indentation, and bullet points.\"},{\"section\":\"Brevity\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Reduce the resume length to 2 pages by removing redundant information.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Create a dedicated skills section listing relevant teaching and management skills.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Use strong action verbs to describe responsibilities and achievements.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Proofread the resume for any grammatical errors or typos.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor the resume to match specific job descriptions by including relevant keywords.\"}]'),(44,'2026-05-14 05:35:06.647442',0x00,25,87,'Mrinank_Resume.pdf','Mrinank Kavuri\n# mrinank1318@gmail.com  +91 9014410150 ð https://www.linkedin.com/in/mrinank-kavuri/\n§ https://github.com/mrinank1301 Ð https://leetcode.com/u/mrinank kavuri/\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nCS undergraduate (Expected 2027) with hands-on experience building and deploying full-stack AI systems on AWS and\nAzure using Next.js, FastAPI, and React. Projects include OrbiCall (100+ concurrent participants) and JobSpring\n(100+ active users), both built end-to-end. Proficient in Python, TypeScript, Docker, LLMs, and distributed\nsystems. 1743 (Top 10%) LeetCode rated in C++, with solid DSA and system design foundations.\nEDUCATION\nParul University 2023 – 2027\nB.Tech in Computer Science (Specialization: AIML)\n• GPA: 8.28/10.0\n• Coursework: Data Structures and Algorithms, Operating Systems, Computer Networking, OOP, DBMS\nPROJECTS\nJobSpring – AI Job Application Automation Platform — React, Firebase, Azure, FastAPI, LLMs 2\n• Built an AI-powered career platform using React 18, TypeScript, FastAPI, and Firebase enabling ATS-\noptimized resume generation, voice mock interviews, and job application automation.\n• Designed a microservices-based backend with Python and OpenAI API to parse job descriptions, generate\nATS-aligned resume bullets via NLP, and render PDFs using ReportLab stored on Azure Blob Storage.\n• Implemented PDF processing and semantic matching using Cosmos DB for resume–JD alignment scoring.\n• Integrated voice interview system using Vapi, ElevenLabs, and Deepgram with Razorpay payment gateway,\nsupporting 100+ active users on Azure App Service with Docker deployment.\n• Led end-to-end development and mentored contributors on system design and AI architecture.\nOrbiCall – AI-Integrated Video Calling Platform —Next.js, AWS, FastAPI 2\n• Developed an AI-powered video conferencing platform using OpenAI API, Next.js 15, and FastAPI, supporting\n100+ participants across 10–15 concurrent rooms with AI assistant response latency of 2–3ms.\n• Integrated a multi-language collaborative code editor using CodeMirror 6 and Yjs with WebSocket-based synchro-\nnization, supporting simultaneous editing across participants with live cursor tracking.\n• Engineered a modular monolithic architecture separating concerns across routers, services, and WebSocket han-\ndlers, enabling independent feature development without microservices overhead.\n• Deployed services on AWS via Docker and Nginx for reverse proxying, load balancing, and service isolation.\nSKILLS\nProgramming Languages: C++, Python, JavaScript/TypeScript, Java, SQL\nFrontend: React, Next.js, HTML5, CSS3, SASS, Tailwind, shadcn/ui\nBackend: Node.js, Express, Spring Boot, FastAPI, REST APIs\nCloud & DevOps: AWS(EC2,S3), Azure, Docker, CI/CD\nDatabases & Tools: MySQL, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Git, IntelliJ, Linux/Unix\nAI/ML: LLMs, Transformers, LangChain, RAG, FAISS/Chroma, Prompt Engineering, Model Fine-tuning\nCore Competencies: Agile development, distributed systems, software deployment, code reviews, testing, debugging\nACHIEVEMENTS\n• Strong competitive programming profile with a 1743 (Top 10%) LeetCode rating, 2-Star CodeChef, and 4-Star\nHackerRank (Problem Solving).\n• Secured a Top 10 position at the Parul HackVerse Hackathon among 100+ teams.\n• Won the Vadodara Startup Festival Idea Competition for developing a user-centric job discovery platform.\nEXTRA-CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES\n• Web Development Lead at DSC, leading student web projects, workshops, and technical mentorship.\n• Core Member of CodexFusion, an AIML-exclusive technical club.\nCERTIFICATIONS\n• Oracle Cloud Infrastructure 2025 Certified Data Science Professional 2\n• Certified Smart Coder by Smart Interviews 2\n\n\n--- Additional content recovered from PDF annotations and alternate parser ---\nParul University\n2023 – 2027\n+91-9014410150\nhttps://leetcode.com/u/mrinank_kavuri/\nhttps://github.com/mrinank1301/Jobspring\nhttps://github.com/mrinank1301/final-yr-project\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1MLRLM_8rhcTYYbQ5v_-7-su6HHkSq7pZ/view?usp=sharing\nhttps://smartinterviews.in/certificate/a227faff','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume demonstrates relevant skills for the candidate\'s field, including Python, TypeScript, Docker, LLMs, Next.js, FastAPI, and React. A job description would allow for a more precise keyword match analysis.\",\"suggestion\":\"Providing a job description would allow for a more precise keyword match analysis.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"5/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume has some formatting issues, including missing spaces between sections and inconsistent bullet symbols. The use of special characters in the contact information may also cause parsing issues. For example, the phone number is separated by a strange character. The LinkedIn and Github links are also separated by strange characters.\",\"suggestion\":\"Ensure consistent spacing between sections and use standard bullet points. Remove special characters from contact information.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"8/10\",\"explanation\":\"Present: Contact, Summary/Objective, Education, Projects/Research, Skills, Achievements, Certifications. Missing: Internships, Coursework.\",\"suggestion\":\"Consider adding an \'Internships\' or \'Coursework\' section to further showcase your experience and knowledge.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume includes some measurable indicators, such as \'100+ concurrent participants\' and \'100+ active users\'. However, some project descriptions are less specific. For example, \'Built an AI-powered career platform\' could be more detailed. \'Led end-to-end development and mentored contributors on system design and AI architecture\' is a good bullet.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify the impact of your projects and use strong action verbs to highlight your accomplishments.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is one page, which is good. However, some bullets could be more concise. The project descriptions are slightly verbose.\",\"suggestion\":\"Trim verbose descriptions and focus on the most impactful details.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\",\"suggestion\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Formatting\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Ensure consistent spacing between sections and use standard bullet points.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify the impact of your projects with specific metrics.\"},{\"section\":\"Projects\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Provide more details about the technologies used and the outcomes achieved in your projects.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Consider adding more specific skills related to your projects.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Proofread the resume for any typos or grammatical errors.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Add an \'Internships\' or \'Coursework\' section to showcase your experience and knowledge.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor your resume to match the keywords in the job description.\"}]'),(45,'2026-05-14 05:38:00.694021',0x01,25,65,'Mrinank_Resume.pdf','Mrinank Kavuri\n# mrinank1318@gmail.com  +91 9014410150 ð https://www.linkedin.com/in/mrinank-kavuri/\n§ https://github.com/mrinank1301 Ð https://leetcode.com/u/mrinank kavuri/\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nCS undergraduate (Expected 2027) with hands-on experience building and deploying full-stack AI systems on AWS and\nAzure using Next.js, FastAPI, and React. Projects include OrbiCall (100+ concurrent participants) and JobSpring\n(100+ active users), both built end-to-end. Proficient in Python, TypeScript, Docker, LLMs, and distributed\nsystems. 1743 (Top 10%) LeetCode rated in C++, with solid DSA and system design foundations.\nEDUCATION\nParul University 2023 – 2027\nB.Tech in Computer Science (Specialization: AIML)\n• GPA: 8.28/10.0\n• Coursework: Data Structures and Algorithms, Operating Systems, Computer Networking, OOP, DBMS\nPROJECTS\nJobSpring – AI Job Application Automation Platform — React, Firebase, Azure, FastAPI, LLMs 2\n• Built an AI-powered career platform using React 18, TypeScript, FastAPI, and Firebase enabling ATS-\noptimized resume generation, voice mock interviews, and job application automation.\n• Designed a microservices-based backend with Python and OpenAI API to parse job descriptions, generate\nATS-aligned resume bullets via NLP, and render PDFs using ReportLab stored on Azure Blob Storage.\n• Implemented PDF processing and semantic match