ensuthar2105 Ð leetcode.com/praveensuthar2105\nSummary\nJava Backend Engineer focused on distributed, service-oriented systems and GenAI integrations. Shipped a live SaaS product scaling\nacross 6 countries and built two production-grade Gemini workflows. Backed by strong CS fundamentals, clean OOP design, and 650+\nLeetCode problems solved. B.Tech CSE (2027), driven to solve complex backend challenges at scale.\nEducation\nB.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering Vadodara, Gujarat\nParul University 2023 – 2027\nHigher Secondary Certificate (HSC) Shivganj, Rajasthan\nModern Defence Senior Secondary School 2022\nProjects\nMockMate [GitHub]\nJava 22, Spring Boot 3, LangChain4j, Gemini API, PostgreSQL, WebSocket, STOMP, Docker, React, TypeScript\n- Designed a distributed, service-oriented mock interview platform; applied OOP design patterns across the question\ngeneration, evaluation, and session management modules to keep each service independently deployable and testable.\n- Built an isolated code execution engine using Docker containers with sandboxed per-submission runtimes supporting Java\nand Python; optimized execution turn-around to 3–5 seconds and preserved user submission history within PostgreSQL to\nprevent processing duplication.\n- Integrated Gemini via LangChain4j for real-time AI evaluation over WebSocket/STOMP at sub-2-second latency;\nauthored JUnit 5 tests covering execution edge cases and instrumented structured logging across all service layers.\nATS Resify [Live] [GitHub]\nJava 22, Spring Boot 3, React, TypeScript, Gemini AI, AWS Elastic Beanstalk, Google Cloud, Docker, GitHub Actions\n- Shipped a full-stack SaaS platform serving 54 active users across 6+ countries; implemented secure authentication via\nJWT and OAuth2 while maintaining decoupled API contract boundaries between the React UI and Spring Boot services.\n- Integrated Gemini AI via a stateless RESTful API for automated resume feedback generation, sustaining stable\nsub-2-second response times under concurrent user traffic.\n- Automated deployment workflows by architecting a full CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions and Docker; deployed\ninfrastructure on AWS Elastic Beanstalk and executed a zero-downtime migration to Google Cloud.\nMediSync [GitHub]\nJava, Spring Boot, React, MySQL, PostgreSQL, Google OAuth 2.0, Gemini AI\n- Engineered a real-time supply chain redistribution engine in Spring Boot to dynamically evaluate live inventory levels\nagainst zone-specific demand thresholds and initiate automated rerouting logic.\n- Applied event-driven architecture to decouple zone demand tracking modules from the central redistribution layer, ensuring\nlinear scaling and high reliability under high-throughput scenarios.\n- Integrated Gemini AI for predictive demand forecasting and protected administration resources via Google OAuth 2.0\nrole-based access tokens to isolate zone admin permissions.\nTechnical Skills\nLanguages: Java, JavaScript, Python, SQL, HTML/CSS\nBackend & Architecture: Spring Boot 3, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, Spring MVC, RESTful API Design,\nWebSocket/STOMP, Service-Oriented Architecture, Event-Driven Architecture\nFrontend: React.js, TypeScript\nAI/ML Integration: Gemini API, LangChain4j, Spring AI, Prompt Engineering\nDatabases: PostgreSQL, MySQL\nDevOps & Cloud: Docker, GitHub Actions, AWS (Elastic Beanstalk, S3), Linux, Maven, Postman\nCS Fundamentals: Data Structures & Algorithms, OOP & Design Patterns, Distributed Systems, Unit Testing (JUnit 5),\nObservability & Logging, CI/CD, Agile/Scrum\nCertifications\n- AWS Academy Cloud Foundations – Amazon Web Services, 2025\n- IBM AI Fundamentals – IBM, 2025\nAchievements & Activities\n- Solved 650+ problems on LeetCode across arrays, trees, graphs, and dynamic programming — consistently optimizing for time\nand space complexity with a focus on scalable algorithm design.\n- Participated in Smart India Hackathon 2024; built and demoed a functional prototype in 24 hours as part of a six-person\nteam, owning the backend architecture end to end.\n\n\n--- Additional content recovered from PDF annotations and alternate parser ---\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/praveensuthar2105/\nhttps://github.com/praveensuthar2105\nhttps://leetcode.com/u/praveensuthar2105/\nhttps://github.com/praveensuthar2105/MockMate\nhttps://atsresify.me/\nhttps://github.com/praveensuthar2105/AI_Powered_Resume_Builder\nhttps://github.com/praveensuthar2105/MediSync','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume demonstrates a good understanding of relevant skills for a backend engineer, including Java, Spring Boot, React, and AI/ML integration. Missing keywords include specific cloud platforms like Azure or GCP, and potentially more detail on specific testing methodologies.\",\"suggestion\":\"Consider adding specific cloud platform experience and expanding on testing methodologies to enhance keyword alignment.\"},\"formatting\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume has minor formatting issues with dense paragraphs instead of bullet points in the summary. The rest of the resume is well-formatted and ATS-safe.\",\"suggestion\":\"Convert the summary into bullet points to improve readability and scannability.\"},\"sectionCompleteness\":{\"score\":\"10/10\",\"explanation\":\"All required sections are present: Contact, Summary, Education, Projects, Technical skills, Certifications, and Achievements.\",\"suggestion\":\"No missing sections.\"},\"impactScore\":{\"score\":\"7/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume includes several projects with measurable indicators, such as \'optimized execution turn-around to 3–5 seconds\' and \'Shipped a full-stack SaaS platform serving 54 active users across 6+ countries\'. However, some descriptions could be more specific about the impact.\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify the impact of each project by including specific metrics and outcomes.\"},\"brevity\":{\"score\":\"10/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume is one page long with concise bullet points and no filler words.\",\"suggestion\":\"The length is appropriate.\"},\"experienceFit\":{\"score\":\"N/A\",\"explanation\":\"No job description provided for comparison.\",\"suggestion\":\"Advice on how to frame experience to better match the target role level.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Convert the summary into bullet points to improve readability and highlight key achievements.\"},{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Quantify the impact of each project by including specific metrics and outcomes.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Consider adding specific cloud platform experience (e.g., Azure, GCP) to enhance keyword alignment.\"},{\"section\":\"Projects\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Use stronger action verbs to describe your contributions and accomplishments.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Proofread the resume for any grammatical errors or typos.\"},{\"section\":\"Keywords\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Expand on testing methodologies to enhance keyword alignment.\"}]'),(54,'2026-05-25 08:59:34.368796',0x00,NULL,87,'euro CV.pdf','Ataklti Haile Tela \nNationality: Ethiopian  Date of birth: 17/12/1987  \nPlace of birth: Rama,Tigray,, Ethiopia  Gender: Male   Phone: (+251) 925055292  \n Email: haileataklti990@yahoo.com  \n Website: https://www.linkedin/in/atakltihaile \n Home: Axum, 2010 Axum (Ethiopia) \nABOUT MYSELF\nI am Civil Engineer with over 10 years of experience in roads, buildings, water supply, and irrigation projects. Skilled\nin site supervision, project leadership, cost management, and quality assurance. Proven record as Construction\nHead, reducing project costs by 12% through efficient resource and cost-control strategies. Proficient in AutoCAD,\nPrimavera, and P6. Multilingual in Tigrinya, Amharic, and English, motivated to apply engineering expertise in\ninternational development and NGO projects.\n \nWORK EXPERIENCE\n @SUR Construction PLC – Mekelle,Tigray, , Ethiopia \nCity: Mekelle,Tigray, |  Country: Ethiopia \nSite engineer & Construction head \n[ 21/10/2014 – Current ] \n1. Construction Head (2024-current)@SUR Construction PLC\nKey Responsibilities\nProject Leadership & Planning\n• Lead the overall construction project from initiation to completion.\n• Develop and control project schedules and milestones.\n• Coordinate design, procurement, and site teams for smooth workflow.\nFinancial & Contract Management\n• Manage budgets, project costs, and cash flow.\n• Approve purchase orders and subcontractor agreements.\n• Monitor variations/claims and report to management or clients.\nTeam & Stakeholder Coordination\n• Supervise and guide site engineers, supervisors, and subcontractors.\n• Act as the main point of contact between clients, consultants, and company management.\n• Resolve disputes and negotiate solutions.\nQuality & Safety Oversight\n• Approve quality plans and ensure compliance with standards.\n• Oversee safety policies across all sites.\n• Make strategic decisions to prevent accidents, delays, or defects.\nReporting & Client Relations\n• Present progress, financial status, and challenges to senior management and clients.\n• Ensure project handover with proper documentation and compliance.\nAchievements\n• Reduced project costs by 12% through efficient resource allocation and cost-control strategies.\n• Delivered milestones ahead of schedule by optimizing work sequencing and monitoring progress.\n• Improved on-site safety performance by 20%, enforcing HSE standards and training staff.\n• Enhanced quality assurance, achieving zero major defects at project handover.\n• Negotiated favorable supplier and subcontractor agreements, increasing profit margins.\n• Mentored junior engineers, strengthening team capability and retention.\n2.Site Engineer (2014-2024)@SUR Construction PLC\nKey Responsibilities\n• Supervised and managed site engineers, foremen, and subcontractors to ensure smooth project execution.\n• Ensured all construction works complied with drawings, specifications, and standards.\n• Monitored progress against schedules, delivering projects within deadlines.\n• Interpreted design drawings, resolved technical issues, and coordinated with consultants.\n• Conducted quality inspections on concrete, rebar, road works, and water systems.\n• Efficiently allocated manpower, equipment, and materials, reducing delays and waste.\n• Enforced health and safety standards, conducted toolbox talks, and ensured PPE compliance.\n• Prepared and submitted detailed progress, inspection, and testing reports.\nEDUCATION AND TRAINING\nCivil Engineering \nMekelle University [ 07/09/2009 – 17/07/2014 ] \nCity: Mekelle |  Country: Ethiopia |  Website: www.mu.edu.et |  Level in EQF: EQF level 6 \nLANGUAGE SKILLS \nMother tongue(s): Tigrigna \nOther language(s): \nAmharic English \nLISTENING C2  READING C2  WRITING C2  LISTENING B1  READING C1  WRITING B1  \nSPOKEN PRODUCTION C2  SPOKEN INTERACTION C2  SPOKEN PRODUCTION A2  SPOKEN INTERACTION A1  \nLevels: A1 and A2: Basic user - B1 and B2: Independent user - C1 and C2: Proficient user\nSKILLS \nPremavira P6 /  AUTOCAD - 2D + 3D /  MS Office (MS Word MS Excel MS PowerPoint MS Access MS Project) /\nProblem solving /  health and safety in the workplace /  Team work /  Time management \n\n\n--- Additional content recovered from PDF annotations and alternate parser ---\nPlace of birth: Rama,Tigray,, Ethiopia  Gender: Male\nPhone: (+251) 925055292 \nEmail: haileataklti990@yahoo.com \nWebsite: https://www.linkedin/in/atakltihaile \nHome: Axum, 2010 Axum (Ethiopia) \nAmharic\nLISTENING C2  READING C2  WRITING C2\nSPOKEN PRODUCTION C2  SPOKEN INTERACTION C2\nEnglish\nLISTENING B1  READING C1  WRITING B1\nSPOKEN PRODUCTION A2  SPOKEN INTERACTION A1\nhttp://www.mu.edu.et','{\"keywordMatch\":{\"score\":\"6/10\",\"explanation\":\"The resume includ