ow to frame experience to better match the target role level.\"}}','[{\"section\":\"Experience\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Rewrite bullet points to focus on quantifiable achievements and outcomes using strong action verbs.\"},{\"section\":\"Formatting\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"suggestion\":\"Replace dense paragraphs with concise bullet points to improve readability and ATS compatibility.\"},{\"section\":\"Skills\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Expand the skills section to include specific construction methodologies, software proficiencies, and industry standards.\"},{\"section\":\"Achievements\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"suggestion\":\"Add a dedicated \'Projects\' or \'Certifications\' section to showcase specific accomplishments or relevant certifications.\"},{\"section\":\"General\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Review the resume for filler words and redundant information to improve conciseness.\"},{\"section\":\"Summary\",\"priority\":\"low\",\"suggestion\":\"Tailor the summary to highlight specific skills and experiences relevant to the target role.\"}]'),(55,'2026-05-25 11:47:45.050028',0x00,NULL,74,'MUHAMMAD SAJID.pdf',' \n  \nMUHAMMAD SAJID                                                                                                                                  \n +92332-8901409 \n +966 550152113 \nPassport # EC5574302 \n  \n \nCareer Objective \nExperienced Telecommunications Professional with over 11 years of expertise in network maintenance, technical \nsupport and problem-solving. Adept at managing network performance targets handling complex service affecting \nalarms and providing technical solutions under pressure. Proficient in SDH, DWDM/MSAN, and Datacenter \noperations  with a strong background in AC and DC power systems and software management. \nNetwork Maintenance: Perform all type of MDTs and TCs, SDH/ DWDM/MSAN/Data center/ PMR/CMR \nTechnical Troubleshooting: AC/DC Power Systems and Transmission (ALU, Huawei, Delta, Cisco, Siemens, lucent)  \nSoftware Proficiency: M2000,U2000 Huawei, ISM2000, NMS, NetCo, OWS, WFMS, IFSM, RTTS, MS Office, \nReporting & Documentation: SLA, CMR, PMR, Daily Outage Reports, Quality audit  \nCustomer Support: Technical support for Telco and Non-Telco issues \nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE \nQuality Control & EHS Coordinator Gulf business Horizons (July 2022 -till present \n• weekly and monthly meetings with the management team to define and refine EHS goals and objectives. \n• Prepared and conducted training programs for employees on health and safety policies, ensuring the best \npractices and regulatory requirements. \n• Perform regular basis OWS, on-site audits and inspections. identify hazards and EHS violations. To ensure \ntimely rectification of identified issues. \n• Prepared and implemented new health and safety protocols and measures to ensure compliance with all \nrelevant regulations and standards. \n• Continuously monitoring the operational processes and employee activities and providing reports on EHS \nperformance and compliance. \n• Prepared comprehensive documentation including risk assessments, incident and accident reports and \nhealth safety manuals to ensure that all records were accurate and up to date. \nField Operation & Maintenance Technician Gulf Business Horizons (June 2019 –June-2022  \n• Performed all types of tickets and shared root causes to ensure downtime and efficient recovery for SDH, \nDWDM, MSAN and Data Centre operations. \n• Network Maintenance: Meet the network performance targets, including SLA, PMR, and CMR metrics to \nensure the best levels of network reliability and performance \n• Alarm Management & Troubleshooting: Managing the work orders and addressing service-affecting \nalarms. Troubleshooting and resolving the issues related to AC and DC power systems and Transmission \ninfrastructure. \n• Installation & Maintenance: Executing installation and maintenance of power shelves, MDT, PAT \nsystems, and transmission equipment from Cisco, Huawei, Siemens, Alcatel-Lucent, Eltek, and Emerson. \n• Software Management: Utilizing RTTS, M2000, U2000 Huawei, ISM2000, NMS, NetCo, OWS, WFMS and \nIFSM, for comprehensive network management and troubleshooting, ensuring accurate data processing \nand effective problem resolution. \n \n \nPMR Coordinator June 2021 Gulf Business Horizons Central Region (20-Nov-2021-Jan-2022) \n• Work Order Management: Manage all Work Orders (WO) to achieve 100% completion targets to ensure \nalignment of WFMS (Workforce Management System) data with OWS every month. \n• Prepared and shared daily PMR (Preventive Maintenance Report) summaries with management. \n• Compiled weekly site audits and distributed quality reports to assess and ensure standards. \n• Preparing monthly consolidated summary reports and presenting them to both management and \ncustomers to provide insights into the performance area for improvement. \n• Identifying any abnormal issues found during PMR and escalating to the customer promptly to ensure \ntimely resolution \n• Managing the staff performance to ensure developing aligns with HR policies and organizational \nstandards. Foster a culture of continuous improvement and professional growth. \n• Monitoring the PMR quality performance of telecom services and developing improvement plans for PMR \nto ensure service quality and reliability. \n \nTechnical support Engineer (2G & 3G, LTE) IN Huawei TECHNOLOGY (PVT) Ltd. Huawei MS Project. \n(Telco, Non-Telco) for North-I Region (Jan-2016 –June-2019) \n• Microwave Transmission Troubleshooting Providing Technical Support to 2G & 3G and 4G LTE Field Teams \nfor Telco & Non-Telco issues. \n• On site Alarm verification and DC power Control panel Troubleshooting, modules & Rectifier controllers  \n• Routine DG (Diesel Generator) and Batteries health check.  \n• DG Installation and mobile DG replacement on Mobile site  \n• Updating daily network report, fault management reports, performance Responsible for Network Outage \nControl and Root cause analysis (RCA). \n• Responsible to Network Maintenance targets in terms of SLAs and OMT Coordinate with Field Engineers \nfor handling the work orders and Power related Service affecting alarms. \n• Proper Co-ordination cycle between the operator and on-field POC\'s Alarms monitoring 24/7 by using I-\nManager U2000 (2G & 3G, LTE) (Huawei Software). \n• Dispatching Trouble Tickets via WFM/OWS (workforce Management) Huawei Software. \nNOC Engineer IN ANDROMEDA TECHNOLOGY (PVT) Ltd. Huawei Project (Non-Telco)  \nFor North-I Region offered by Ufone (01-October-2015 December-2015) \n• Microwave Transmission Troubleshooting Providing Technical Support to 2G & 3G Field Teams for Telco & \nNon-Telco issues. \n• Updating daily network reports, fault management reports and performance Responsible for Network \nOutage Control and Root cause analysis (RCA). \n• Responsible for Network Maintenance targets in terms of SLAs and OMT Coordinate with Field Engineers \nfor handling the work orders and Service affecting alarms. \n• Proper Coordination cycle between the operator and on-field POC\'s Alarms monitoring 24/7 by using I-\nManager U2000 (2G & 3G) (Huawei Software). \n• Dispatching Trouble Tickets via WFM/OWS (workforce Management) Huawei Software. \nNOC Engineer IN Hi-tech Networks (PVT) Ltd AS Night shift Team Lead. Huawei Project (Non-Telco) for \nNorth-II Region offered by Ufone (15-July-2012 TO Sep-2015) \n• Responsible for Network Outage Control and Root cause analysis (RCA) Updating daily network reports, \nfault management reports, performance SLA (Service Level Agreement) PM (Preventive Maintains) \nReports & CM (corrective Maintains) Reports of Huawei MS project Tickets closed on the daily basis by \nusing Huawei CBOM Applications. \n• Responsible to Network Maintenance targets in terms of SLAs and OMT and Coordinated with Field \nEngineers for handling the work orders and Service-affecting alarms. \n